<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="566" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-09"><hi rend="italic">September 9,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Translated letters found on Mooradian mark him as a revolutionary
                            emissary. No evidence of his armed resistance to the Turkish Government
                            on Turkish soil. I demanded his instant release on the ground that his
                            imprisonment was unauthorized. He is surrendered to me to be kept from
                            correspondence until I can send him out of Turkey.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>